    • Constructor Detail

      • EncodedPayload

        public EncodedPayload​(@Nonnull
                      ToDataOutput content,
                      long minimalLength)
        Creates a new payload which encodes the given ToDataOutput into an byte array beforehand. Warning, this constructor should be only used if you want to evaluate the content of the message in other simulators outside of the application simulator. Please prefer the method EncodedPayload(long, long) if the evaluate is not needed. This method can cause a high memory consumption.

      • EncodedPayload

      • EncodedPayload

        public EncodedPayload​(@Nonnull
                      byte[] bytes,
                      long minimalLength)
        Creates a new payload using the full byte array with an minimal payload length. Warning, this constructor should be only used if you want to evaluate the content of the message in other simulators, outside of the application simulator. Please prefer the method EncodedPayload(long, long) if the evaluate is not needed. This method can cause a high memory consumption.
        Parameters:
        bytes - the message payload.
        minimalLength - Unit: [bytes].

      • EncodedPayload

        public EncodedPayload​(long lengthInBytes,
                      long minimalLength)
        Creates a new encoded message using the size of the payload length with an minimal payload length.
        Parameters:
        lengthInBytes - the actual length of the message's payload. Unit: [bytes].
        minimalLength - the minimal assumed length of the message's payload. Unit: [bytes].

      • decodePayload

        public final <T extends ToDataOutput> T decodePayload()
                                               throws IllegalStateException
        Tries to decode the payload byte array into the original object. This only works if this object has been initialized with a implementation of ToDataOutput.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the object type to decode the byte array to
        Returns:
        the decoded object of type T.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if something went wrong during decoding
